# Styling Conventions

## Tailwind CSS Usage
- The project uses Tailwind CSS with custom theme configuration
- Global styles are defined in [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css)
- Custom theme variables use OKLCH color space for better color reproduction
- Responsive design uses standard Tailwind breakpoints:
  - `sm`: 640px and up
  - `md`: 768px and up
  - `lg`: 1024px and up
  - `xl`: 1280px and up

## Custom Utilities
- `.gradient-title` - Creates a gradient text effect with blue to green colors
- `.dotted-background` - Creates a dotted background pattern
- Use transition utilities like `transition-all duration-300` for smooth animations

## Dark Mode
- Dark mode is supported using the `.dark` class variant
- Custom color variables are defined for both light and dark modes
- Use the theme variables (e.g., `bg-background`, `text-foreground`) for consistent theming
